NXGEN Technology AG
Network Time Protocol (NTP) Client Configuration
Guide
NTP client configuration ensures accurate time synchronization with NXGEN NTP Servers on devices like
Teltonika routers and Hikvision NVR devices. The NTP Server connects only with devices connected via VPN to
Nxgen. This guide outlines the steps to configure NTP clients on these devices with a specified NTP server
address.
Teltonika Router NTP Client Configuration:
By default, the Teltonika router blocks DNS resolution. If we intend to use DNS as the NTP server, we need to
allow DNS resolution by disabling "Rebind protection" in the DNS options. Follow these steps:
1. Access Router Web Interface:
Open a web browser and enter the router's IP address. Log in with your credentials.
2. Navigate to Network > DNS.
Turn off "Rebind protection"
Save and apply the changes.
NXGEN NTP Server Private DNS Address (for VPN Customers):
1. time1.nxgen.cloud
2. time2.nxgen.cloud
NXGEN NTP Server Public DNS Address ( for non VPN connections):
1. timeext1.nxgen.cloud
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/portal/en/kb/articles/network-time-protocol-ntp-client-configuration-guide
Configure NTP:
1. Navigate to NTP Settings:
2. Find the "System" or "Services" section in the router's web interface.
Look for NTP settings or a similar option.
3. Configure NTP Server:
Enter the multiple NTP server address sections:
Hostname: time1.nxgen.cloud
Hostname: time2.nxgen.cloud
Specify the synchronization interval if available (e.g., every 3600 seconds or 60 mins for hourly
synchronization).
Save or Apply changes.
Hikvision NVR NTP Client Configuration:
1. Access NVR Web Interface:
Launch a web browser and enter the NVR's IP address. Log in using your credentials.
2. Navigate to System Settings:
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/portal/en/kb/articles/network-time-protocol-ntp-client-configuration-guide
Look for the "Configuration" or "System Settings" option.
3. Configure NTP Settings:
Locate the NTP settings on “Time Settings” section.
Enter the NTP server address: time1.nxgen.cloud
Specify the synchronization interval if available (e.g., every 3600 seconds for hourly
synchronization).
Save or Apply changes.
 
 
Dahua Device NTP Client Configuration:
1. Access NVR Web Interface:
Launch a web browser and enter the NVR's IP address. Log in using your credentials.
2. Navigate to System Settings:
Look for the "Configuration" or "System" option.
3. Configure NTP Settings:
Locate the NTP settings on “Date&Time” section.
Enter the NTP server address: time1.nxgen.cloud
Specify the synchronization interval if available (e.g., every 3600 seconds for hourly
synchronization).
Save or Apply changes.
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/portal/en/kb/articles/network-time-protocol-ntp-client-configuration-guide
Additional Considerations:
1. Firewall Settings:
Ensure that there are no firewall rules blocking NTP traffic to and from the specified NTP server
(time1.nxgen.cloud, time2.nxgen.cloud).
2. Time Zone Settings:
Verify and configure the correct time zone settings on the devices to ensure accurate time
synchronization.
https://helpdesk.nxgen.io/portal/en/kb/articles/network-time-protocol-ntp-client-configuration-guide
